      },
      "source": [
        "# Tokenization\n",
        "### Simple whitespace tokenization"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 2,
      "id": "e556c9cf",
      "metadata": {

      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Whitespace Tokenization: ['Hello', 'world!', 'This', 'is', 'an', 'example', 'sentence', 'which', 'will', 'demonstrate', 'tokenization.']\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "tokens_whitespace = text.split()\n",
        "print(\"Whitespace Tokenization:\", tokens_whitespace)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "4d2d2ff1",
      "metadata": {

      },
      "source": [
        "### Advanced Tokenization "
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 3,
      "id": "fc456f6d",
      "metadata": {

      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "NLTK:\t ['Hello', 'world', '!', 'This', 'is', 'an', 'example', 'sentence', 'which', 'will', 'demonstrate', 'tokenization', '.']\n",
            "BERT:\t ['hello', 'world', '!', 'this', 'is', 'an', 'example', 'sentence', 'which', 'will', 'demonstrate', 'token', '##ization', '.']\n",
            "GPT-2:\t ['Hello', 'Ġworld', '!', 'ĠThis', 'Ġis', 'Ġan', 'Ġexample', 'Ġsentence', 'Ġwhich', 'Ġwill', 'Ġdemonstrate', 'Ġtoken', 'ization', '.']\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "from nltk.tokenize import word_tokenize\n",
        "from transformers import AutoTokenizer\n",
        "\n",
        "tokens_nltk_word = word_tokenize(text)\n",
        "print(\"NLTK:\\t\", tokens_nltk_word)\n",
        "\n",
        "bert_tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(\"bert-base-uncased\")\n",
        "gpt2_tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(\"gpt2\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Tokenize using BERT tokenizer\n",
        "bert_tokens = bert_tokenizer.tokenize(text)\n",
        "print(\"BERT:\\t\", bert_tokens)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Tokenize using GPT-2 tokenizer\n",
        "gpt2_tokens = gpt2_tokenizer.tokenize(text)\n",
        "print(\"GPT-2:\\t\", gpt2_tokens)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 4,
      "id": "031fbadb",
      "metadata": {

      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",

            "['hello', 'world!', 'this', 'is', 'an', 'exampl', 'sentenc', 'which', 'will', 'demonstr', 'tokenization.']\n",

            "['hello', 'world', '!', 'this', 'is', 'an', 'exampl', 'sentenc', 'which', 'will', 'demonstr', 'token', '##izat', '.']\n",
            "['hello', 'ġworld', '!', 'ġthis', 'ġis', 'ġan', 'ġexampl', 'ġsentenc', 'ġwhich', 'ġwill', 'ġdemonstr', 'ġtoken', 'izat', '.']\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "from nltk.stem.snowball import EnglishStemmer\n",
        "\n",
        "stemmer = EnglishStemmer()\n",
        "\n",
        "print([ stemmer.stem(token) for token in tokens_whitespace ])\n",
        "print([ stemmer.stem(token) for token in tokens_nltk_word ])\n",
        "print([ stemmer.stem(token) for token in bert_tokens ])\n",
        "print([ stemmer.stem(token) for token in gpt2_tokens ])"
      ]
    },

        "# Word Embedding "

      },

        {

            "Token embeddings shape: torch.Size([1, 16, 768])\n",
            "tensor([[[-0.4287, -0.4912, -0.3842,  ..., -0.6163,  0.0652,  0.8848],\n",
            "         [-0.1895,  0.0180,  0.2054,  ..., -0.1912,  0.2703,  0.4201],\n",
            "         [-0.0318, -0.4484,  0.6803,  ..., -0.7846, -0.5227,  0.4743],\n",

            "         [-0.4928, -0.4659, -0.4742,  ..., -0.4532, -0.7805,  0.7394],\n",
            "         [ 0.6777, -0.0224, -0.6548,  ...,  0.1915, -0.8439, -0.3038],\n",
            "         [ 0.5562, -0.0230, -0.5201,  ...,  0.2985, -0.9937, -0.2383]]],\n",
            "       grad_fn=\u003CNativeLayerNormBackward0\u003E)\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "from transformers import AutoModel\n",
        "import torch\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load model\n",
        "model = AutoModel.from_pretrained(\"bert-base-uncased\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Tokenize and get embeddings\n",
        "inputs = bert_tokenizer(text, return_tensors=\"pt\")\n",
        "\n",
        "embeddings = model(**inputs).last_hidden_state\n",
        "\n",
        "# Get embeddings for each token\n",
        "print(\"Token embeddings shape:\", embeddings.shape)\n",
        "print(embeddings)"
      ]
    },

      "cell_type": "code",

      },

            "this\t[ 2.279593  -2.1956666]\n",

          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n",
        "\n",
        "# Reduce dimensionality of embeddings since visualizing 768 dimensions is quite hard\n",
        "pca = PCA(n_components=2)\n",
        "reduced_embeddings = pca.fit_transform(embeddings[0].detach().numpy())\n",
        "for t, e in zip(bert_tokens, reduced_embeddings):\n",
        "    print(f'{t}\\t{e}')"
      ]

      "source": [
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plot embeddings\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))\n",
        "for i, token in enumerate(bert_tokens):\n",

        "plt.title(\"Token Embeddings (Reduced to 2D)\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"PCA Component 1\")\n",

      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "word_pairs = [\n",
        "    ('Table', 'running'),\n",
        "    ('mountain', 'keyboard'),\n",
        "    ('shoe', 'banana'),\n",
        "    ('ocean', 'telephone'),\n",
        "    ('guitar', 'Paper'),\n",
        "    ('king', 'queen'),\n",
        "    ('man', 'woman'),\n",
        "    ('Car', 'vehicle'),\n",
        "    ('apple', 'fruit'),\n",
        "    ('dog', 'puppy'),\n",
        "]"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 9,
      "id": "036c5fe3",
      "metadata": {

      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Cosine similarity between 'Table' and 'running':\t0.924914\n",
            "Cosine similarity between 'mountain' and 'keyboard':\t0.936766\n",
            "Cosine similarity between 'shoe' and 'banana':\t0.975347\n",
            "Cosine similarity between 'ocean' and 'telephone':\t0.865625\n",
            "Cosine similarity between 'guitar' and 'Paper':\t0.761284\n",
            "Cosine similarity between 'king' and 'queen':\t0.982673\n",
            "Cosine similarity between 'man' and 'woman':\t0.975454\n",
            "Cosine similarity between 'Car' and 'vehicle':\t0.980615\n",
            "Cosine similarity between 'apple' and 'fruit':\t0.941876\n",
            "Cosine similarity between 'dog' and 'puppy':\t0.964794\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity\n",
        "\n",
        "# Function to get the embedding for a single word\n",
        "def get_embedding(word):\n",
        "    inputs = bert_tokenizer(word, return_tensors=\"pt\")\n",
        "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
        "        embedding = model(**inputs).last_hidden_state\n",
        "    return embedding[0][0].numpy()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calculate cosine similarity between embeddings of each word pair\n",
        "for word1, word2 in word_pairs:\n",
        "    emb1 = get_embedding(word1)\n",
        "    emb2 = get_embedding(word2)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Compute cosine similarity\n",
        "    similarity = cosine_similarity([emb1], [emb2])[0][0]\n",
        "    \n",
        "    print(f\"Cosine similarity between '{word1}' and '{word2}':\\t{similarity:.6f}\")"
      ]
    },

        "words = ' '.join([ w for a, b in word_pairs for w in [ a, b ] ])\n",
